benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/bundles/{bundleId}/tags - Retrieve bundle tags

covered: Valid Request: Happy-path GET returns 200 with a JSON array of Tag objects; Content-Type application/json verified.
Empty Response: Existing bundle with no tags returns 200 and an empty array.

Query Parameters: includedDeleted true/false and default behavior covered; audit=FULL and audit=MINIMAL covered; combined params covered; invalid audit value rejected; extra/unknown param tolerated; basic injection attempt handled.
Path Parameter Validation: Invalid UUID format returns 400.
Authorization: 401 for missing and invalid tokens.
Reliability/Performance: Large dataset, concurrent requests, degraded dependency (200/504), and API unavailability (503/504) covered.
Backward compatibility: No audit parameter path exercised (though not asserting absence of audit details).
gaps: Audit default NONE: No explicit scenario for audit=NONE or assertions that audit fields are absent when audit is omitted/defaulted.
Authorization 403: No test for insufficient permissions/roles resulting in 403.
Rate Limiting/Throttling: No scenarios to trigger/verify 429 responses and Retry-After headers under burst traffic.
Caching/Conditional GET: No verification of ETag/Last-Modified/Cache-Control headers or conditional requests (If-None-Match/If-Modified-Since leading to 304).
Pagination: Not addressed. Likely not applicable for this endpoint; confirm with API spec. If supported, add tests; if not, assert absence of pagination headers and full return.
Schema/Contract Validation: No strict validation of Tag schema and audit payload shapes across FULL/MINIMAL/NONE against the API definition.
Input Validation Edge Cases: No tests for includedDeleted non-boolean values (e.g., includedDeleted=foo/1), audit case sensitivity (e.g., full vs FULL), duplicate or empty query params.
Server Error Handling: No explicit test for 500 Internal Server Error responses and client behavior.
Content Negotiation: No tests for Accept header handling (e.g., unsupported Accept leading to 406).
recommendations: Add scenarios asserting audit=NONE explicitly and that omitting audit yields no audit fields (default NONE).
Introduce a 403 Forbidden scenario for authenticated users lacking required permissions/scopes.
Design a rate-limiting test: burst requests to provoke 429, then assert Retry-After and rate-limit headers.
Add caching tests: verify ETag/Cache-Control headers on 200; perform conditional GET (If-None-Match/If-Modified-Since) and expect 304 when appropriate.
Clarify pagination support in the spec. If supported, add page/limit tests and large dataset navigation; if not, add a test asserting no pagination headers and complete result set.
Incorporate contract/schema validation against the OpenAPI for Tag objects and audit fields per audit level (FULL/MINIMAL/NONE).
Expand input validation: includedDeleted with invalid values, audit case sensitivity and whitespace, duplicate query params precedence.
Add a reliability test simulating backend failure to return 500 and verify error body/headers and retry/logging behavior.
Add content negotiation tests: Accept: application/json succeeds; unsupported Accept returns 406.
